## Common Usage Patterns

### Pattern 1: New Feature Development

```bash
# 1. Plan the feature
python -m tapps_agents.cli planner plan "Add user authentication"

# 2. Enhance the prompt (optional but recommended)
python -m tapps_agents.cli enhancer enhance "Add user authentication"

# 3. Design the system
python -m tapps_agents.cli architect design "Authentication system architecture"

# 4. Design the API
python -m tapps_agents.cli designer design-api "Authentication API"

# 5. Implement
python -m tapps_agents.cli implementer implement "Authentication service" auth_service.py

# 6. Test
python -m tapps_agents.cli tester test auth_service.py

# 7. Review
python -m tapps_agents.cli reviewer review auth_service.py
```

### Pattern 2: Bug Fix

```bash
# 1. Debug the error
python -m tapps_agents.cli debugger debug "Error message" --file buggy.py --line 42

# 2. Fix the code
python -m tapps_agents.cli implementer refactor buggy.py "Fix the bug"

# 3. Test
python -m tapps_agents.cli tester test buggy.py

# 4. Review
python -m tapps_agents.cli reviewer score buggy.py
```

### Pattern 3: Code Quality Improvement

```bash
# 1. Analyze current quality
python -m tapps_agents.cli reviewer report . json markdown html

# 2. Improve code
python -m tapps_agents.cli improver improve file.py "Refactor for better maintainability"

# 3. Verify improvement
python -m tapps_agents.cli reviewer score file.py
```

### Pattern 4: Security Audit

```bash
# 1. Security audit
python -m tapps_agents.cli ops audit-security .

# 2. Review findings
python -m tapps_agents.cli reviewer review --security .

# 3. Fix issues
python -m tapps_agents.cli implementer refactor vulnerable.py "Fix security issues"
```

